{{Wikipedia}}
==English==

===Noun===
'''jade'''

# (''uncountable'') A semiprecious stone either [[nephrite]] or [[jadite]], generally green or white in color, often used for carving figurines.
#(''colour'') A grayish shade of green, typical of jade stones.
#:<table><tr><td>jade colour: &nbsp;</td><td bgcolor="#79896C" width="80">&nbsp; </td></tr></table>
# A horse too old to be put to work.
# A woman, especially in contempt.

====Quotations====
'''Late 1500's'''

''Beatrice:'' You always end with a jade's trick: I know you of old. <br/>
&mdash; William Shakespeare, ''Much Ado About Nothing''

